 {"id": "bd-go-2", "title": "PORT: getopt sub-bead 2 \u2014 GetoptState + step_short scanner", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "task", "epic": "bd-go-epic", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T09:23:30.478978Z", "resolution": "Added crates/frankenlibc-core/src/getopt/state.rs with pure-safe Rust GetoptState (optind/nextchar/optopt/optarg via ArgRef indirection \u2014 no raw pointers) and step_short() driver. Handles bundled short opts, required arg attached/separated, missing-required (\"?\" or \":\" silent mode), unknown opts, GNU optional \"::\", \"--\" terminator, lone-dash stop. 15 unit tests pass alongside the 10 parse tests from bd-go-1."}
+{"id": "bd-go-3", "title": "PORT: getopt sub-bead 3 \u2014 wire abi shim to core::getopt::step_short", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "task", "epic": "bd-go-epic", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T09:25:54.594452Z", "resolution": "Replaced ~140 lines of pointer-arithmetic short-option scanner in unistd_abi.rs::parse_getopt_short with a thin marshalling shim that builds argv as Vec<&[u8]>, syncs GetoptState to/from the libc_optind/libc_optopt/libc_optarg externs and a static GETOPT_NEXTCHAR: Option<ArgRef>, and delegates to frankenlibc_core::getopt::step_short. Local GetoptArgMode/getopt_arg_mode/getopt_prefers_colon helpers removed (now imported from core). parse_getopt_long updated to call core::getopt_prefers_colon and to use Option<ArgRef> for nextchar reset. All 3 conformance_diff_getopt tests pass; 173/173 abi lib tests pass."}
+{"id": "bd-go-epic", "title": "PORT: getopt native Rust impl", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "epic", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T09:25:54.594452Z", "resolution": "Epic complete in 3 sub-beads. bd-go-1: core::getopt::parse helpers (10 tests). bd-go-2: core::getopt::state machine (15 tests). bd-go-3: abi shim wired to core::getopt::step_short (3 conformance tests pass). Net effect: ~140 lines of unsafe pointer arithmetic in unistd_abi.rs replaced by ~50 lines of marshalling over a pure-safe Rust state machine in core. The short-option scanner is now layout-independent and unit-testable in isolation."}

